label: A6B16C_cI46_229_e_ch_a-001
title: Dy$_{6}$Fe$_{16}$O Structure
comments:
This is a \href{current_web_home_dir/A_cI2_229_a-001}{body-centered cubic structure} with vacancies on the octahedral sites adjacent to the oxygen atoms. 
 The (2a) site is often only partially occupied, {\em e.g.}, Ca$_{6}$Ag$_{16}$N was originally thought to be Ag$_{8}$Ca$_{3}$ (Calvert, 1964), but there is some nitrogen present on the (2a) site. (Villars, 2004)
